          <msContents>
            <summary>Poem in 6 verses (ṣaṭpadī) dedicated to the Hindu deity Viṣṇu traditionally attributed to the medieval Indian sage Śaṅkarācārya; contains reference Viṣṇu's avatāras and other myths associated with the god; the secondary title Ṣaṭpadī is sometimes translated as "the bees" (insect with 6 legs).</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
